{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to open by quoting Einstein's wonderful statement,"},{"time":4000,"text":"just so people will feel at ease that the great scientist of the 20th century"},{"time":9000,"text":"also agrees with us, and also calls us to this action."},{"time":13000,"text":"He said, \"A human being is a part of the whole, called by us, the 'universe,' --"},{"time":18000,"text":"a part limited in time and space."},{"time":21000,"text":"He experiences himself, his thoughts and feelings,"},{"time":24000,"text":"as something separated from the rest,"},{"time":27000,"text":"a kind of optical delusion of his consciousness."},{"time":31000,"text":"This delusion is a kind of prison for us,"},{"time":34000,"text":"restricting us to our personal desires and to affection for a few persons nearest to us."},{"time":40000,"text":"Our task must be to free ourselves from this prison by widening our circle of compassion,"},{"time":46000,"text":"to embrace all living creatures and the whole of nature in its beauty.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"This insight of Einstein's is uncannily close to that of Buddhist psychology,"},{"time":55000,"text":"wherein compassion -- \"karuna,\" it is called --"},{"time":59000,"text":"is defined as, \"the sensitivity to another's suffering"},{"time":62000,"text":"and the corresponding will to free the other from that suffering.\""},{"time":67000,"text":"It pairs closely with love, which is the will for the other to be happy,"},{"time":71000,"text":"which requires, of course, that one feels some happiness oneself"},{"time":75000,"text":"and wishes to share it."},{"time":78000,"text":"This is perfect in that it clearly opposes self-centeredness"},{"time":81000,"text":"and selfishness to compassion, the concern for others,"},{"time":85000,"text":"and, further, it indicates that those caught in the cycle of self-concern"},{"time":90000,"text":"suffer helplessly, while the compassionate are more free"},{"time":94000,"text":"and, implicitly, more happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"The Dalai Lama often states that compassion is his best friend."},{"time":101000,"text":"It helps him when he is overwhelmed with grief and despair."},{"time":104000,"text":"Compassion helps him turn away from the feeling of his suffering"},{"time":108000,"text":"as the most absolute, most terrible suffering anyone has ever had"},{"time":113000,"text":"and broadens his awareness of the sufferings of others,"},{"time":116000,"text":"even of the perpetrators of his misery and the whole mass of beings."},{"time":121000,"text":"In fact, suffering is so huge and enormous,"},{"time":124000,"text":"his own becomes less and less monumental."},{"time":127000,"text":"And he begins to move beyond his self-concern into the broader concern for others."},{"time":133000,"text":"And this immediately cheers him up,"},{"time":135000,"text":"as his courage is stimulated to rise to the occasion."},{"time":139000,"text":"Thus, he uses his own suffering"},{"time":141000,"text":"as a doorway to widening his circle of compassion."},{"time":145000,"text":"He is a very good colleague of Einstein's, we must say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"Now, I want to tell a story,"},{"time":151000,"text":"which is a very famous story in the Indian and Buddhist tradition,"},{"time":154000,"text":"of the great Saint Asanga"},{"time":156000,"text":"who was a contemporary of Augustine in the West"},{"time":159000,"text":"and was sort of like the Buddhist Augustine."},{"time":161000,"text":"And Asanga lived 800 years after the Buddha's time."},{"time":165000,"text":"And he was discontented with the state of people's practice"},{"time":168000,"text":"of the Buddhist religion in India at that time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"And so he said, \"I'm sick of all this. Nobody's really living the doctrine."},{"time":174000,"text":"They're talking about love and compassion and wisdom and enlightenment,"},{"time":177000,"text":"but they are acting selfish and pathetic."},{"time":180000,"text":"So, Buddha's teaching has lost its momentum."},{"time":183000,"text":"I know the next Buddha will come a few thousand years from now,"},{"time":186000,"text":"but exists currently in a certain heaven\" -- that's Maitreya --"},{"time":190000,"text":"\"so, I'm going to go on a retreat and I'm going to meditate"},{"time":193000,"text":"and pray until the Buddha Maitreya reveals himself to me,"},{"time":197000,"text":"and gives me a teaching or something"},{"time":199000,"text":"to revive the practice of compassion in the world today.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"So he went on this retreat. And he meditated for three years"},{"time":206000,"text":"and he did not see the future Buddha Maitreya."},{"time":208000,"text":"And he left in disgust."},{"time":211000,"text":"And as he was leaving, he saw a man --"},{"time":214000,"text":"a funny little man sitting sort of part way down the mountain."},{"time":217000,"text":"And he had a lump of iron."},{"time":220000,"text":"And he was rubbing it with a cloth."},{"time":222000,"text":"And he became interested in that."},{"time":224000,"text":"He said, \"Well what are you doing?\""},{"time":226000,"text":"And the man said, \"I'm making a needle.\""},{"time":231000,"text":"And he said, \"That's ridiculous. You can't make a needle"},{"time":233000,"text":"by rubbing a lump of iron with a cloth.\""},{"time":235000,"text":"And the man said, \"Really?\" And he showed him a dish full of needles."},{"time":238000,"text":"So he said, \"Okay, I get the point.\""},{"time":240000,"text":"He went back to his cave. He meditated again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"Another three years, no vision. He leaves again."},{"time":246000,"text":"This time, he comes down."},{"time":248000,"text":"And as he's leaving, he sees a bird making a nest on a cliff ledge."},{"time":252000,"text":"And where it's landing to bring the twigs to the cliff,"},{"time":256000,"text":"its feathers brushes the rock -- and it had cut the rock"},{"time":260000,"text":"six to eight inches in. There was a cleft in the rock"},{"time":263000,"text":"by the brushing of the feathers of generations of the birds."},{"time":266000,"text":"So he said, \"All right. I get the point.\" He went back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"Another three years."},{"time":270000,"text":"Again, no vision of Maitreya after nine years."},{"time":272000,"text":"And he again leaves, and this time: water dripping,"},{"time":275000,"text":"making a giant bowl in the rock where it drips in a stream."},{"time":279000,"text":"And so, again, he goes back. And after 12 years there is still no vision."},{"time":283000,"text":"And he's freaked out. And he won't even look left or right"},{"time":285000,"text":"to see any encouraging vision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287000,"text":"And he comes to the town. He's a broken person."},{"time":290000,"text":"And there, in the town, he's approached by a dog"},{"time":293000,"text":"who comes like this -- one of these terrible dogs you can see in some poor countries,"},{"time":298000,"text":"even in America, I think, in some areas --"},{"time":300000,"text":"and he's looking just terrible."},{"time":302000,"text":"And he becomes interested in this dog because it's so pathetic,"},{"time":305000,"text":"and it's trying to attract his attention. And he sits down looking at the dog."},{"time":308000,"text":"And the dog's whole hindquarters are a complete open sore."},{"time":313000,"text":"Some of it is like gangrenous,"},{"time":315000,"text":"and there are maggots in the flesh. And it's terrible."},{"time":318000,"text":"He thinks, \"What can I do to fix up this dog?"},{"time":321000,"text":"Well, at least I can clean this wound and wash it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":324000,"text":"So, he takes it to some water. He's about to clean,"},{"time":326000,"text":"but then his awareness focuses on the maggots."},{"time":330000,"text":"And he sees the maggots, and the maggots are kind of looking a little cute."},{"time":333000,"text":"And they're maggoting happily in the dog's hindquarters there."},{"time":336000,"text":"\"Well, if I clean the dog, I'll kill the maggots. So how can that be?"},{"time":340000,"text":"That's it. I'm a useless person and there's no Buddha, no Maitreya,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and everything is all hopeless."},{"time":345000,"text":"And now I'm going to kill the maggots?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"So, he had a brilliant idea."},{"time":350000,"text":"And he took a shard of something, and cut a piece of flesh from his thigh,"},{"time":355000,"text":"and he placed it on ground."},{"time":357000,"text":"He was not really thinking too carefully about the ASPCA."},{"time":361000,"text":"He was just immediately caught with the situation."},{"time":363000,"text":"So he thought, \"I will take the maggots and put them on this piece of flesh,"},{"time":366000,"text":"then clean the dog's wounds, and then"},{"time":369000,"text":"I'll figure out what to do with the maggots.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":372000,"text":"So he starts to do that. He can't grab the maggots."},{"time":374000,"text":"Apparently they wriggle around. They're kind of hard to grab, these maggots."},{"time":378000,"text":"So he says, \"Well, I'll put my tongue on the dog's flesh."},{"time":382000,"text":"And then the maggots will jump on my warmer tongue\" --"},{"time":384000,"text":"the dog is kind of used up --"},{"time":386000,"text":"\"and then I'll spit them one by one down on the thing.\""},{"time":389000,"text":"So he goes down, and he's sticking his tongue out like this."},{"time":392000,"text":"And he had to close his eyes, it's so disgusting, and the smell and everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397000,"text":"And then, suddenly, there's a pfft, a noise like that."},{"time":399000,"text":"He jumps back and there, of course, is the future Buddha Maitreya"},{"time":403000,"text":"in a beautiful vision -- rainbow lights, golden, jeweled, a plasma body,"},{"time":410000,"text":"an exquisite mystic vision -- that he sees."},{"time":412000,"text":"And he says, \"Oh.\" He bows."},{"time":414000,"text":"But, being human, he's immediately thinking of his next complaint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"So as he comes up from his first bow he says,"},{"time":420000,"text":"\"My Lord, I'm so happy to see you, but where have you been for 12 years?"},{"time":424000,"text":"What is this?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"And Maitreya says, \"I was with you. Who do you think was making needles"},{"time":429000,"text":"and making nests and dripping on rocks for you, mister dense?\""},{"time":433000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":435000,"text":"\"Looking for the Buddha in person,\" he said."},{"time":438000,"text":"And he said, \"You didn't have, until this moment, real compassion."},{"time":444000,"text":"And, until you have real compassion, you cannot recognize love.\""},{"time":447000,"text":"\"Maitreya\" means love, \"the loving one,\" in Sanskrit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451000,"text":"And so he looked very dubious, Asanga did."},{"time":453000,"text":"And he said, \"If you don't believe me, just take me with you.\""},{"time":456000,"text":"And so he took the Maitreya -- it shrunk into a globe, a ball --"},{"time":461000,"text":"took him on his shoulder."},{"time":463000,"text":"And he ran into town in the marketplace, and he said, \"Rejoice! Rejoice!"},{"time":467000,"text":"The future Buddha has come ahead of all predictions. Here he is.\""},{"time":471000,"text":"And then pretty soon they started throwing rocks and stones at him --"},{"time":474000,"text":"it wasn't Chautauqua, it was some other town --"},{"time":477000,"text":"because they saw a demented looking, scrawny looking yogi man,"},{"time":481000,"text":"like some kind of hippie, with a bleeding leg and a rotten dog on his shoulder,"},{"time":486000,"text":"shouting that the future Buddha had come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"So, naturally, they chased him out of town."},{"time":490000,"text":"But on the edge of town, one elderly lady, a charwoman in the charnel ground,"},{"time":495000,"text":"saw a jeweled foot on a jeweled lotus on his shoulder and then the dog,"},{"time":499000,"text":"but she saw the jewel foot of the Maitreya, and she offered a flower."},{"time":503000,"text":"So that encouraged him, and he went with Maitreya."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"Maitreya then took him to a certain heaven,"},{"time":508000,"text":"which is the typical way a Buddhist myth unfolds."},{"time":511000,"text":"And Maitreya then kept him in heaven for five years,"},{"time":513000,"text":"dictating to him five complicated tomes"},{"time":517000,"text":"of the methodology of how you cultivate compassion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"And then I thought I would share with you what that method is, or one of them."},{"time":523000,"text":"A famous one, it's called the \"Sevenfold Causal Method of Developing Compassion.\""},{"time":528000,"text":"And it begins first by one meditating and visualizing that all beings are with one --"},{"time":535000,"text":"even animals too, but everyone is in human form."},{"time":539000,"text":"The animals are in one of their human lives. The humans are human."},{"time":542000,"text":"And then, among them, you think of your friends and loved ones, the circle at the table."},{"time":547000,"text":"And you think of your enemies, and you think of the neutral ones."},{"time":550000,"text":"And then you try to say, \"Well, the loved ones I love."},{"time":554000,"text":"But, you know, after all, they're nice to me."},{"time":556000,"text":"I had fights with them. Sometimes they were unfriendly."},{"time":558000,"text":"I got mad. Brothers can fight. Parents and children can fight."},{"time":561000,"text":"So, in a way, I like them so much because they're nice to me."},{"time":565000,"text":"While the neutral ones I don't know. They could all be just fine."},{"time":569000,"text":"And then the enemies I don't like because they're mean to me."},{"time":573000,"text":"But they are nice to somebody. I could be them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":576000,"text":"And then the Buddhists, of course, think that, because we've all had infinite previous lives,"},{"time":580000,"text":"we've all been each other's relatives, actually."},{"time":584000,"text":"Therefore all of you, in the Buddhist view,"},{"time":586000,"text":"in some previous life, although you don't remember it and neither do I,"},{"time":590000,"text":"have been my mother -- for which I do apologize for the trouble I caused you."},{"time":595000,"text":"And also, actually, I've been your mother."},{"time":598000,"text":"I've been female, and I've been every single one of yours' mother in a previous life,"},{"time":601000,"text":"the way the Buddhists reflect."},{"time":603000,"text":"So, my mother in this life is really great. But all of you in a way"},{"time":606000,"text":"are part of the eternal mother."},{"time":609000,"text":"You gave me that expression; \"the eternal mama,\" you said. That's wonderful."},{"time":613000,"text":"So, that's the way the Buddhists do it."},{"time":615000,"text":"A theist Christian can think that all beings, even my enemies, are God's children."},{"time":620000,"text":"So, in that sense, we're related."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622000,"text":"So, they first create this foundation of equality."},{"time":625000,"text":"So, we sort of reduce a little of the clinging to the ones we love --"},{"time":629000,"text":"just in the meditation -- and we open our mind to those we don't know."},{"time":633000,"text":"And we definitely reduce the hostility and the \"I don't want to be compassionate to them\""},{"time":637000,"text":"to the ones we think of as the bad guys, the ones we hate and we don't like."},{"time":642000,"text":"And we don't hate anyone, therefore. So we equalize. That's very important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"And then the next thing we do is what is called \"mother recognition.\""},{"time":649000,"text":"And that is, we think of every being as familiar, as family."},{"time":654000,"text":"We expand. We take the feeling about remembering a mama,"},{"time":659000,"text":"and we defuse that to all beings in this meditation."},{"time":663000,"text":"And we see the mother in every being."},{"time":665000,"text":"We see that look that the mother has on her face,"},{"time":668000,"text":"looking at this child that is a miracle"},{"time":670000,"text":"that she has produced from her own body, being a mammal,"},{"time":673000,"text":"where she has true compassion, truly is the other, and identifies completely."},{"time":677000,"text":"Often the life of that other will be more important to her than her own life."},{"time":681000,"text":"And that's why it's the most powerful form of altruism."},{"time":684000,"text":"The mother is the model of all altruism for human beings,"},{"time":688000,"text":"in spiritual traditions."},{"time":691000,"text":"And so, we reflect until we can sort of see that motherly expression in all beings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"People laugh at me because, you know, I used to say that"},{"time":700000,"text":"I used to meditate on mama Cheney as my mom,"},{"time":704000,"text":"when, of course, I was annoyed with him about all of his evil doings in Iraq."},{"time":709000,"text":"I used to meditate on George Bush. He's quite a cute mom in a female form."},{"time":712000,"text":"He has his little ears and he smiles and he rocks you in his arms."},{"time":715000,"text":"And you think of him as nursing you."},{"time":718000,"text":"And then Saddam Hussein's serious mustache is a problem,"},{"time":721000,"text":"but you think of him as a mom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724000,"text":"And this is the way you do it. You take any being who looks weird to you,"},{"time":726000,"text":"and you see how they could be familiar to you."},{"time":730000,"text":"And you do that for a while, until you really feel that."},{"time":734000,"text":"You can feel the familiarity of all beings."},{"time":736000,"text":"Nobody seems alien. They're not \"other.\""},{"time":738000,"text":"You reduce the feeling of otherness about beings."},{"time":741000,"text":"Then you move from there to remembering the kindness of mothers in general,"},{"time":746000,"text":"if you can remember the kindness of your own mother,"},{"time":748000,"text":"if you can remember the kindness of your spouse,"},{"time":750000,"text":"or, if you are a mother yourself, how you were with your children."},{"time":753000,"text":"And you begin to get very sentimental; you cultivate sentimentality intensely."},{"time":758000,"text":"You will even weep, perhaps, with gratitude and kindness."},{"time":761000,"text":"And then you connect that with your feeling that everyone has that motherly possibility."},{"time":765000,"text":"Every being, even the most mean looking ones, can be motherly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"And then, third, you step from there to what is called \"a feeling of gratitude.\""},{"time":774000,"text":"You want to repay that kindness that all beings have shown to you."},{"time":778000,"text":"And then the fourth step, you go to what is called \"lovely love.\""},{"time":782000,"text":"In each one of these you can take some weeks, or months, or days"},{"time":784000,"text":"depending on how you do it, or you can do them in a run, this meditation."},{"time":788000,"text":"And then you think of how lovely beings are when they are happy,"},{"time":793000,"text":"when they are satisfied."},{"time":795000,"text":"And every being looks beautiful when they are internally feeling a happiness."},{"time":799000,"text":"Their face doesn't look like this. When they're angry, they look ugly, every being,"},{"time":803000,"text":"but when they're happy they look beautiful."},{"time":805000,"text":"And so you see beings in their potential happiness."},{"time":808000,"text":"And you feel a love toward them and you want them to be happy, even the enemy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811000,"text":"We think Jesus is being unrealistic"},{"time":813000,"text":"when he says, \"Love thine enemy.\""},{"time":817000,"text":"He does say that, and we think he's being unrealistic"},{"time":820000,"text":"and sort of spiritual and highfalutin. \"Nice for him to say it, but I can't do that.\""},{"time":823000,"text":"But, actually, that's practical."},{"time":825000,"text":"If you love your enemy that means you want your enemy to be happy."},{"time":828000,"text":"If your enemy was really happy, why would they bother to be your enemy?"},{"time":832000,"text":"How boring to run around chasing you."},{"time":834000,"text":"They would be relaxing somewhere having a good time."},{"time":837000,"text":"So it makes sense to want your enemy to be happy,"},{"time":839000,"text":"because they'll stop being your enemy because that's too much trouble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842000,"text":"But anyway, that's the \"lovely love. \""},{"time":844000,"text":"And then finally, the fifth step is compassion, \"universal compassion.\""},{"time":848000,"text":"And that is where you then look at the reality of all the beings you can think of."},{"time":854000,"text":"And you look at them, and you see how they are."},{"time":856000,"text":"And you realize how unhappy they are actually, mostly, most of the time."},{"time":860000,"text":"You see that furrowed brow in people."},{"time":862000,"text":"And then you realize they don't even have compassion on themselves."},{"time":865000,"text":"They're driven by this duty and this obligation."},{"time":867000,"text":"\"I have to get that. I need more. I'm not worthy. And I should do something.\""},{"time":871000,"text":"And they're rushing around all stressed out."},{"time":873000,"text":"And they think of it as somehow macho, hard discipline on themselves."},{"time":877000,"text":"But actually they are cruel to themselves."},{"time":880000,"text":"And, of course, they are cruel and ruthless toward others."},{"time":882000,"text":"And they, then, never get any positive feedback."},{"time":884000,"text":"And the more they succeed and the more power they have,"},{"time":886000,"text":"the more unhappy they are."},{"time":888000,"text":"And this is where you feel real compassion for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891000,"text":"And you then feel you must act."},{"time":894000,"text":"And the choice of the action, of course,"},{"time":896000,"text":"hopefully will be more practical"},{"time":900000,"text":"than poor Asanga, who was fixing the maggots on the dog"},{"time":904000,"text":"because he had that motivation, and whoever was in front of him,"},{"time":907000,"text":"he wanted to help."},{"time":909000,"text":"But, of course, that is impractical. He should have founded the ASPCA in the town"},{"time":913000,"text":"and gotten some scientific help for dogs and maggots."},{"time":916000,"text":"And I'm sure he did that later. (Laughter) But that just indicates the state of mind, you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"And so the next step -- the sixth step beyond \"universal compassion\" --"},{"time":926000,"text":"is this thing where you're linked with the needs of others in a true way,"},{"time":930000,"text":"and you have compassion for yourself also,"},{"time":933000,"text":"and it isn't sentimental only. You might be in fear of something."},{"time":936000,"text":"Some bad guy is making himself more and more unhappy"},{"time":939000,"text":"being more and more mean to other people"},{"time":941000,"text":"and getting punished in the future for it in various ways."},{"time":944000,"text":"And in Buddhism, they catch it in the future life."},{"time":947000,"text":"Of course in theistic religion they're punished by God or whatever."},{"time":950000,"text":"And materialism, they think they get out of it just by not existing,"},{"time":952000,"text":"by dying, but they don't."},{"time":955000,"text":"And so they get reborn as whatever, you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958000,"text":"Never mind. I won't get into that."},{"time":960000,"text":"But the next step is called \"universal responsibility.\""},{"time":963000,"text":"And that is very important -- the Charter of Compassion"},{"time":966000,"text":"must lead us to develop through true compassion,"},{"time":969000,"text":"what is called \"universal responsibility.\""},{"time":971000,"text":"In the great teaching of his Holiness the Dalai Lama"},{"time":975000,"text":"that he always teaches everywhere, he says"},{"time":977000,"text":"that that is the common religion of humanity: kindness."},{"time":980000,"text":"But \"kindness\" means \"universal responsibility.\""},{"time":982000,"text":"And that means whatever happens to other beings is happening to us:"},{"time":986000,"text":"we are responsible for that, and we should take it"},{"time":990000,"text":"and do whatever we can at whatever little level"},{"time":992000,"text":"and small level that we can do it."},{"time":994000,"text":"We absolutely must do that. There is no way not to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998000,"text":"And then, finally, that leads to a new orientation in life"},{"time":1002000,"text":"where we live equally for ourselves and for others"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and we are"},{"time":1010000,"text":"joyful and happy."},{"time":1012000,"text":"One thing we mustn't think is that compassion makes you miserable."},{"time":1015000,"text":"Compassion makes you happy."},{"time":1017000,"text":"The first person who is happy when you get great compassion is yourself,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"even if you haven't done anything yet for anybody else."},{"time":1023000,"text":"Although, the change in your mind already does something for other beings:"},{"time":1028000,"text":"they can sense this new quality in yourself,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"and it helps them already, and gives them an example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033000,"text":"And that uncompassionate clock has just showed me that it's all over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1037000,"text":"So, practice compassion, read the charter, disseminate it"},{"time":1042000,"text":"and develop it within yourself."},{"time":1044000,"text":"Don't just think, \"Well, I'm compassionate,\" or \"I'm not compassionate,\""},{"time":1047000,"text":"and sort of think you're stuck there."},{"time":1049000,"text":"You can develop this. You can diminish the non-compassion,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"the cruelty, the callousness, the neglect of others,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"and take universal responsibility for them."},{"time":1058000,"text":"And then, not only will God smile and the eternal mama will smile,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"but Karen Armstrong will smile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1065000,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}